Third-party material bundled with rfair
========================================

rfair itself is released under the MIT License (see the LICENSE file). The
package additionally bundles reference data and rubrics derived from external
projects. Each is redistributed under its own license, reproduced or referenced
below. The bundled artifacts live in R/sysdata.rda and inst/extdata/ and are
generated from the upstream sources by the scripts in data-raw/.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. F-UJI (FAIRsFAIR Research Data Object Assessment service)
   Source:  https://github.com/pangaea-data-publisher/fuji
   DOI:     https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3775793
   Holder:  PANGAEA / FAIRsFAIR
   License: MIT
   Use:     metric definitions (metrics_v0.x.yaml), and the reference tables
            for SPDX licenses, file formats, access rights, communication
            protocols, and metadata standards.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. SPDX License List
   Source:  https://github.com/spdx/license-list-data
   Holder:  The Linux Foundation
   License: CC0-1.0
   Use:     the bundled SPDX license identifier and name tables.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. (Re)usable Data Project rubric
   Source:  https://reusabledata.org
   Holder:  The (Re)usable Data Project
   License: CC-BY-4.0
   Use:     the license-reusability taxonomy and curated repository ratings
            used by license_reuse() and reusabledata_rating().

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. FAIR principle definitions
   Source:  https://peta-pico.github.io/FAIR-nanopubs/principles/
            referenced by https://www.go-fair.org/fair-principles/
   Holder:  GO FAIR / FAIR-nanopubs contributors
   License: CC-BY-4.0
   Use:     the canonical FAIR principle text returned by fair_principles()
            and principle_definition().

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The full text of the MIT, CC0-1.0, and CC-BY-4.0 licenses is available from the
SPDX License List at https://spdx.org/licenses/. No upstream copyright notice
has been removed; this file records provenance and licensing for the bundled
components as required for redistribution.
